folder: Central Park West & 87th Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
(1)
Central Park West, west side, from 87th to 89th Streets. The Mohonk and Minnewaska Apartments, shown at the S.W. corner of 88th Street, have been demolished and replaced by a modern apartment house. The Walden School is on the N.W. corner of 88th Street and beyond it is the St. Urban. These buildings are still standing (1935).
February 2, 1929.

P. L. Sperr, Photographer.

(2)
The same, from a somewhat greater distance.
February 2, 1929.

P. L. Sperr, Photographer.

THE NEW YORK

folder: Central Park West & 87th Street (West), Manhattan, NY
text:
Central Park, West, west side, north from and including West 87th Street. Note surface car and tracks, soon after replaced by busses. A portion of Central Park appears on the right.

June 28, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.
